Worried by the spate of kidnapping activities in Osun State, the state governor, Gboyega Oyetola, yesterday launched aggressive combatant security forces to checkmate the inhuman acts. In addition, zonal joint action against the rising spate of insecurity and criminality has also been taken by the governors of the South-West states of Osun, Ondo, Ekiti, Oyo, Ogun and Lagos.  The chief press secretary to the governor, Mr. Adeniyi Adesina, who made this known in a statement in Osogbo, disclosed that, the combatant security force was launched after a security meeting where recent incidents were reviewed and decisions taken to halt further attacks in any part of the state. He, however, stressed that all the South-West governors met yesterday in Abuja, to finetune the arrangement.  The statement further explained that, heads of security and paramilitary outfits in the state â€“ The Police, the Army, the Air Force, the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), the Department of State Services (DSS) and the Nigerian Immigration Service (NIS) were all present at the meeting.